Amazing fun I'm a guy who's who is boosted when I watch myself to goofy things...haha, but seriously. This app is seriously the BEST! I can finally find hilarious one liners or bits from songs and make stupid and funny short clips and share them with really whoever I want. My friends and family do goofy ones back and it is seriously he highlight of my day just to get a solid laugh here or there. They even make it so you can upload some of your own recordings and make a dubsmash of that. The iPhone doesn't let you have music on it and use the camcorder at the same time, and this all basically solves that while also making it easy to save all the dubsmash videos you've done.

My all-time favorite unnecessary app! Plain and simply put, when it comes to sheer entertainment value and having a laugh among friends, Dubsmash is my favorite app. The novelty never really gets old whether you're lip-syncing to a song or lip-syncing a famous line from your favorite movie, this app stays fresh. I've tried other apps to try and find more options to waste away lazy afternoons, but they ultimately waste space and grow stale (Trivia Crack, I'm looking at you). Yes it's true, there are a lot of bugs and crashes with the latest version, but that's going to happen when you start taking an app that is initially designed for sharing among the Facebook community, and you start making it into an app that has its own friend list and its own mini social network built into it. Six months ago you pretty much had to have a Facebook account to use this app but today you could have a standalone Dubsmash account if you didn't want Facebook to be the final destination for your creation. To me, a big indicator of an app's ability to contend and to stand on its own two feet, is its ability to be fully functional on its own, without insisting users have a Facebook, Twitter, Tumblr or Google+ account linked to the app for it to function properly. I have confidence Dubsmash will work out the bugs which is why I give this incredibly entertaining app a full 5‚≠êÔ∏è!

Omg...hours of fun! Love it. I'm not one to write reviews, I think this is maybe the third or fourth review I've written thus far. Normally I give the stars, and that's it, lol. However I felt the need to give Dubsmash a big thumbs up. It's so much fun, you can add your own sounds or use one submitted by other users. I can see this becoming a very popular app, like it's not already, and hope to see new features added as it grows. I just hope it won't be one of those apps that after it blows up, they change everything good about it, lol. It's solid the way it is. Would be nice to have more options in the edit section, like maybe the possibility of user created content. Overall I highly recommend this app. It's very entertaining, easy to use, and the end results will get plenty of laughs from anyone you share it with. I also suggest this app to friends and family.

So fun! So, there are a couple of negatives, but man is this app fun...and addictive!  The 2 negatives are: 1) The way it's organized isn't perfect. For example, there are tons of folders that have nothing in them. It would be nice if some kind of icon alerted you to that & you wouldn't waste your time looking in it.  Also, doing a search one way often will not return a result, but will another way. For example, you look for a song by a certain artist & you find it by the artist, but not the song title, or vice-versa.  It would be great if when posting something, the person posting could tag it with key words, not necessarily that show, but that are used for searching for it.  It would speed up the search process enormously!! 2) The app occasionally freezes...probably because I'm workin' it so hard!  All that being said, it's still an absolute blast and you WILL have fun!!

Newset update is extremely slow The Dubsmash app was working fine on my phone until I downloaded themost recent update. Ever since then Dubsmash has slowed to an almost unusable crawl. The audio clip previews take a good while to load, whereas before the loaded pretty much instantly. Switching from one menu option to another is a crap shoot. Sometimes tapping works, other times it won't (but even if it does respond, there's always a delay, unlike before the update). Scrolling through my videos also has issues. Besides taking a bit to start playing, they tend to freeze up and won't let me scroll to another video until the current one finishes playing at least once through (with no way to pause). Ans because of the slowness and response delays, any Dubsmash I record since the update comes out choppy and out of sync no matter what. I generally enjoy Dubsmash, but this particular version of the app is a mess. How it made it's way to the app store in it's current state is a little baffling. I hope these issues get fixed relatively soon, because I would really would like to continue making Dubsmashes.

A Day Changer! I discovered this app the same day I was told my vocal cords were paralyzed and may never speak again. The next day I had several doctor appointments and started using this app to express how I was feeling before, during and after each appointment. Using songs like "get knocked down again" and "I will survive"... I can sincerely say the ease of use and the silliness of it all, instantly restored my JOY! It changed my day from a long day of doctor appointments to a day of  "photo shoots". It didn't change my diagnosis but it certainly changed my day and how I approached the journey ahead of me! LOVE THIS APP! It gives me a voice!

Upvote/Downvote feature would make it way better! So fun, with tons of potential - HOWEVER, all the sounds are terribly organized. Because the sounds are user-submitted there are bad quality, duplicated, and/or misspelled or badly-titled recordings that make the app difficult to enjoy. Sounds just aren't capitalized properly or even categorized and I have to go through hundreds of recordings before finding the exact one I want. I know you can report bad sounds, but even this takes too long. I think the app should develop upvotes or downvotes (like reddit or yikyak), that way good quality recordings go to the top and bad/irrelevant ones get lost in the bottom. I think that's the most efficient way of making this work and keeping it user-based.
